column5: It,s a game really. Chasing the fishies.LOL
nothing like playing a video game on a saturday morning

Ya it didnt matter what depth we fished,they were there. 70 fow and shallower. Im getting the hang of the new machine. I was even able to get rid of the clutter from the greaser beside me. Interfernce was nadda. problem.
Looks like lots of good pike bait!
Not from this lake.LOL  Hey Terry,how about those kick a ss electric augers EH.
electric augers?  never heard of them   we had 3 holes before the gas one got started, and no one heard us cutting them, everyone near did drop by  to see where they could buy them
What we drill,40 50 holes. Not bad I say.  When I get the new drill pack,it will do more.
Those dam Rock Bass I say! lol
What we drill,40 50 holes. Not bad I say.  When I get the new drill pack,it will do more.  Bring it up here @ the end of February and see how many holes you can drill with it.
Bring it up here @ the end of February and see how many holes you can drill with it.    NOT
At least you had fish to play with!!!!
That'll be one of the first video games my boy learns how to play!

Gotta love playing with them fishies my wife hates when I do that at the black of the boat if we are anchored. The best part I found was that all the pickerel here in our river are not on bottom in the winter. Years ago when I first started to use my unit on the ice I was rewarded right away by it showing me fish 6-8' off the bottom in 16 FOW I brought up my line and bam right away I had a 28"  Thanks for posting Brian I have not been out ice fishing in years so its nice to watch someone else have fun
